WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.517 --> 00:00:04.616
So. what is it?
What? What? What?

2
00:00:04.617 --> 00:00:05.822
Spirit. demon. what?

3
00:00:07.164 --> 00:00:08.366
I don't know.

4
00:00:08.368 --> 00:00:10.639
What is it?
I don't know.

5
00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:11.918
Oh. yeah. we're goo positive.

6
00:00:11.942 --> 00:00:13.542
What does that mean?
What does that mean?

7
00:00:13.696 --> 00:00:14.588
It's not like it's an exact science.

8
00:00:17.067 --> 00:00:18.372
Dude. what the hell?

9
00:00:18.374 --> 00:00:20.449
I don't know.

10
00:00:21.917 --> 00:00:23.256
No. seriously.
what the hell?

11
00:00:23.258 --> 00:00:25.442
I don't know.

12
00:00:25.444 --> 00:00:28.759
One theory. any theory.
Uh...

13
00:00:29.676 --> 00:00:31.963
Who are you?
Name's Cole.

14
00:00:31.964 --> 00:00:35.049
I did two tours in Iraq.
Special Ops. Darfur...

15
00:00:35.051 --> 00:00:36.175
And your older brother.
Dean...

16
00:00:36.177 --> 00:00:37.179
Where is he?!

17
00:00:37.181 --> 00:00:39.316
...he and I.
we go way back.

18
00:00:39.318 --> 00:00:42.015
What I do...
is hunt monsters.

19
00:00:42.017 --> 00:00:43.888
You've got
a family. Cole.

20
00:00:43.890 --> 00:00:46.028
I'm guessing
they need you to come back.

21
00:00:46.030 --> 00:00:48.203
and they need you
to come back whole.

22
00:00:48.205 --> 00:00:49.468
Dad!

23
00:00:49.470 --> 00:00:50.877
Dean Winchester
murdered my father.

24
00:00:50.879 --> 00:00:52.405
That was not
your father. Cole.

25
00:00:52.407 --> 00:00:53.709
Your dad was a monster.

26
00:00:53.711 --> 00:00:55.077
What kind of monster
was he?

27
00:00:55.079 --> 00:00:56.517
I don't know.

28
00:00:56.519 --> 00:00:59.422
Never seen that kind before.
never seen it again.

29
00:02:06.361 --> 00:02:10.361
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Supernatural 10x15 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Things They Carried</font>
Original Air Date on March 18. 2015

30
00:02:10.385 --> 00:02:16.885
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

31
00:02:28.346 --> 00:02:31.374
Hey. check it out.
Hey.

32
00:02:33.078 --> 00:02:34.475
Porn?

33
00:02:34.477 --> 00:02:36.610
What?
No. I-it's nothing.

34
00:02:36.612 --> 00:02:38.009
Hey. look.
no judgement from me.

35
00:02:38.011 --> 00:02:39.576
Just. you know.
not where we eat.

36
00:02:39.578 --> 00:02:40.648
Dude. it wasn't porn.

37
00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:42.080
Okay. "erotica."
Whatever.

38
00:02:42.082 --> 00:02:44.152
Zip it up.
Check this out.

39
00:02:45.690 --> 00:02:48.823
The Vic was trained
in Krav Maga and jiu-jitsu.

40
00:02:48.825 --> 00:02:50.553
Still ended up
with her organs drained.

41
00:02:50.555 --> 00:02:53.259
and the marrow was sucked
completely out of the bones.

42
00:02:55.030 --> 00:02:58.269
So...cannibalism.

43
00:02:58.271 --> 00:02:59.669
You thinking a Rugaru?

44
00:02:59.671 --> 00:03:02.267
Or a God. maybe.

45
00:03:03.437 --> 00:03:05.570
I'll go dig up
my pencil-neck suit.

46
00:03:06.779 --> 00:03:08.377
Wait. wait. wait.
W-what?

47
00:03:08.379 --> 00:03:11.114
What. is this not weird enough
for you?

48
00:03:12.252 --> 00:03:15.049
Well. yeah. it's weird.
but. um. I mean. we -- we...

49
00:03:15.051 --> 00:03:17.184
I mean...

50
00:03:19.248 --> 00:03:22.420
Great. 10 minutes.
I'll meet you in the car.

51
00:03:24.156 --> 00:03:26.123
Great.

52
00:03:34.964 --> 00:03:38.265
Sam.

53
00:03:38.267 --> 00:03:40.399
I know what you're doing
over there. and it ain't porn.

54
00:03:43.104 --> 00:03:46.405
Look. man. we have checked
every website. okay?

55
00:03:46.407 --> 00:03:48.101
We've checked it twice.

56
00:03:48.103 --> 00:03:51.707
Sammy.
when we work a case.

57
00:03:51.709 --> 00:03:55.041
there's always that --
that point...

58
00:03:55.043 --> 00:03:58.440
when we have to
face the truth. right?

59
00:04:00.113 --> 00:04:03.613
Even if we don't like it.

60
00:04:04.982 --> 00:04:07.807
Well. truth is...

61
00:04:07.809 --> 00:04:09.738
there's no way
around this.

62
00:04:11.440 --> 00:04:15.832
We saw what happened
to Cain. okay?

63
00:04:15.834 --> 00:04:20.406
I'm not happy about it.
But I got to move on.

64
00:04:23.543 --> 00:04:25.540
So I'm gonna keep doing
what we do --

65
00:04:25.542 --> 00:04:28.106
while I still can.

66
00:04:28.108 --> 00:04:30.913
And I'd like you
to be there with me.

67
00:04:44.555 --> 00:04:47.549
All right.

68
00:05:13.464 --> 00:05:15.630
Agents. I gather.

69
00:05:17.166 --> 00:05:18.531
Uh. was it the suits.

70
00:05:18.533 --> 00:05:20.761
or do we give off
some sort of a Fed stench?

71
00:05:20.763 --> 00:05:22.432
I-it's the suits.

72
00:05:22.434 --> 00:05:24.734
What can I do
for you boys?

73
00:05:24.736 --> 00:05:26.565
Well. uh.
we are here investigating

74
00:05:26.567 --> 00:05:28.533
the death
of private Jacki Prescott.

75
00:05:28.535 --> 00:05:30.899
Shoot. You drove
all the way down from D.C.?

76
00:05:30.901 --> 00:05:32.370
Mm-hmm.
Yeah. we did.

77
00:05:32.372 --> 00:05:34.400
Well. then sorry
to waste your time. agents.

78
00:05:34.402 --> 00:05:36.031
but we wrapped
that one up.

79
00:05:36.033 --> 00:05:38.902
Guy that did it was
a special forces officer --

80
00:05:38.904 --> 00:05:41.206
Rick Willis.

81
00:05:41.208 --> 00:05:43.478
What makes you so sure
it was him?

82
00:05:43.480 --> 00:05:45.510
His fingerprints were
all over the storage room

83
00:05:45.512 --> 00:05:47.078
out on the base
where he did it.

84
00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:49.981
He even left his dog tags
by the body.

85
00:05:49.983 --> 00:05:51.682
So. is he in custody?

86
00:05:52.651 --> 00:05:55.546
No. bastard drank
a boatload of gasoline.

87
00:05:55.548 --> 00:05:56.954
then lit himself on fire.

88
00:05:58.387 --> 00:05:59.689
Well. that's a hell
of a way to go.

89
00:05:59.691 --> 00:06:02.521
No kidding.
Left a wife and a baby.

90
00:06:02.523 --> 00:06:05.593
Third suicide we seen
in six months.

91
00:06:05.595 --> 00:06:07.257
Military town.

92
00:06:09.331 --> 00:06:10.833
Would you like some cake?

93
00:06:10.835 --> 00:06:12.433
Mm. Yeah.

94
00:06:12.435 --> 00:06:14.336
No. uh. y-you know what?
Uh. we're okay.

95
00:06:14.338 --> 00:06:16.032
No. it's really good.
My partner made it.

96
00:06:16.034 --> 00:06:18.968
It looks great. but we're --
no. we're all right.

97
00:06:20.307 --> 00:06:21.777
Uh. we do have
one more question.

98
00:06:21.779 --> 00:06:24.480
Were there any bite marks
found on the body?

99
00:06:24.482 --> 00:06:29.354
No. Vic was killed
with a Bowie.

100
00:06:29.356 --> 00:06:31.953
Well. sheriff.
thank you for your time.

101
00:06:31.955 --> 00:06:33.457
Yeah.

102
00:06:33.459 --> 00:06:36.456
No bite marks.
That rules out Rugaru.

103
00:06:36.458 --> 00:06:37.825
So what? A God?

104
00:06:37.827 --> 00:06:39.224
I don't like
the sound of that.

105
00:06:39.226 --> 00:06:41.526
The guy Molotov-cocktailed
himself.

106
00:06:41.528 --> 00:06:42.830
That's bonkers.

107
00:06:42.832 --> 00:06:45.691
That's like
demon-possession bonkers.

108
00:06:49.365 --> 00:06:50.730
Rick did it.

109
00:06:50.732 --> 00:06:54.365
I'm not trying to say
that he didn't.

110
00:06:54.367 --> 00:06:55.660
But...

111
00:06:55.662 --> 00:06:58.035
I mean. he just got back
from deployment.

112
00:06:58.037 --> 00:07:00.769
and we've all seen what
it can do to a soldier's mind.

113
00:07:00.771 --> 00:07:03.463
My Rick...

114
00:07:04.537 --> 00:07:08.469
...when he's home and good...

115
00:07:08.471 --> 00:07:11.402
I have to kill the spiders.
you know?

116
00:07:15.538 --> 00:07:18.176
Rick was a kind soul.

117
00:07:19.514 --> 00:07:22.049
He never took more life
than he had to.

118
00:07:23.780 --> 00:07:27.953
Did you. um. notice
anything strange. weird.

119
00:07:27.955 --> 00:07:30.656
like. uh...
violent mood swings?

120
00:07:30.658 --> 00:07:32.719
Or weird smells?

121
00:07:33.889 --> 00:07:37.222
No. But...

122
00:07:38.664 --> 00:07:41.693
...Rick was -- he was so --

123
00:07:41.695 --> 00:07:43.094
He was thirsty.

124
00:07:43.096 --> 00:07:44.630
Thirsty for what?

125
00:07:44.632 --> 00:07:46.269
Water.

126
00:07:46.271 --> 00:07:50.102
He'd spend half the day drinking
from the garden hose.

127
00:07:50.104 --> 00:07:52.941
And then. one night.
I caught him in the tub

128
00:07:52.943 --> 00:07:55.742
drinking the bathwater.

129
00:07:55.744 --> 00:07:57.046
When I told him to stop.

130
00:07:57.048 --> 00:07:59.478
it was like
he couldn't even hear me.

131
00:07:59.480 --> 00:08:03.749
And his skin.
it got so dry it bled.

132
00:08:03.751 --> 00:08:05.749
Did he see a doctor?

133
00:08:05.751 --> 00:08:07.085
I took him to the V.A..

134
00:08:07.087 --> 00:08:10.893
but he just got on a list
to get on a list.

135
00:08:10.895 --> 00:08:13.596
And then.
he stopped talking...

136
00:08:13.598 --> 00:08:15.932
And just wasn't himself.

137
00:08:17.462 --> 00:08:21.867
I thought maybe it was PTSD.

138
00:08:26.507 --> 00:08:29.073
Uh. we're very sorry.

139
00:08:32.546 --> 00:08:34.944
You said that Rick
was recently deployed.

140
00:08:34.946 --> 00:08:36.575
Do you have any idea
where?

141
00:08:38.415 --> 00:08:41.446
No. that stuff is classified.

142
00:08:41.448 --> 00:08:43.749
They don't even
let the wives in on it.

143
00:08:43.751 --> 00:08:45.949
Right.

144
00:08:45.951 --> 00:08:48.389
Okay.
well. we'll. um...

145
00:08:48.391 --> 00:08:50.422
We'll leave you alone now.
but if something comes up.

146
00:08:50.424 --> 00:08:52.125
anything at all.
just give us a call.

147
00:08:52.127 --> 00:08:53.725
There's one other thing.

148
00:08:55.030 --> 00:08:57.459
I ran into my friend Jemma
at the supermarket.

149
00:08:57.461 --> 00:09:01.393
She's married to Kit Verson.
a guy from Rick's team.

150
00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:08.475
She thinks Kit came back
different this time.

151
00:09:08.477 --> 00:09:11.140
Kind of felt like we were
dealing with the same thing.

152
00:09:12.814 --> 00:09:14.813
Thank you.

153
00:09:19.457 --> 00:09:23.055
Kit's been going
through some stuff for sure.

154
00:09:23.057 --> 00:09:24.991
Um. you know.
it takes him a while

155
00:09:24.993 --> 00:09:28.109
to get back to normal.
but he always does.

156
00:09:28.134 --> 00:09:29.065
Thanks.

157
00:09:29.066 --> 00:09:31.031
And what about you?
How are you holding up?

158
00:09:31.033 --> 00:09:33.999
I'm okay...

159
00:09:34.001 --> 00:09:35.439
For the most part.

160
00:09:35.441 --> 00:09:39.608
You know. what happened
to Rick and Beth. it...

161
00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:43.877
It's been hard.

162
00:09:45.244 --> 00:09:48.944
"There but for the grace
of God." you know?

163
00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:57.251
Um...May we speak
with your husband?

164
00:09:59.178 --> 00:10:03.348
He. um...
He went out last night.

165
00:10:03.350 --> 00:10:05.211
but he should be back
any minute.

166
00:10:05.213 --> 00:10:07.682
You know. Kit. he comes back
from these deployments.

167
00:10:07.684 --> 00:10:09.480
and he needs his space.

168
00:10:09.482 --> 00:10:10.952
So he's been out
all night?

169
00:10:10.954 --> 00:10:14.950
Well...Yeah.

170
00:10:18.023 --> 00:10:20.788
God.

171
00:10:20.790 --> 00:10:22.491
I can't even
convince myself.

172
00:10:22.493 --> 00:10:24.458
Um...

173
00:10:24.460 --> 00:10:26.425
I'm worried.

174
00:10:26.427 --> 00:10:28.456
This isn't like him.

175
00:10:28.458 --> 00:10:30.296
Has he been thirsty.

176
00:10:30.298 --> 00:10:33.368
like "drink out of the dog bowl"
thirsty?

177
00:10:34.938 --> 00:10:36.968
How did you know?

178
00:10:45.879 --> 00:10:48.139
Recognized
your wheels.

179
00:10:49.749 --> 00:10:51.349
What the hell
are you doing here?

180
00:10:51.351 --> 00:10:52.845
Jemma called me in.

181
00:10:52.847 --> 00:10:54.854
I've known Kit
since we were military brats

182
00:10:54.856 --> 00:10:57.287
raisin' hell
on the same base.

183
00:10:57.289 --> 00:10:58.887
He's a good man.

184
00:11:00.194 --> 00:11:01.992
Well. no one's saying
he's not.

185
00:11:01.994 --> 00:11:03.633
Oh. really. now?

186
00:11:03.635 --> 00:11:05.755
So. what are you two. uh.
here for. Jemma's sweet tea?

187
00:11:07.206 --> 00:11:09.438
You want to tell me
why you're really here?

188
00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:10.711
We're working a case.

189
00:11:10.713 --> 00:11:12.712
Oh. Kit's case?

190
00:11:12.714 --> 00:11:14.480
Honestly.
we're not sure just yet.

191
00:11:14.482 --> 00:11:17.016
but. um.
it's looking like it.

192
00:11:17.018 --> 00:11:19.415
Mm. Says you.

193
00:11:20.984 --> 00:11:23.557
There's a murder-suicide
in town.

194
00:11:23.559 --> 00:11:26.250
Your buddy Kit?
Same unit as the killer.

195
00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:28.458
Same whacked-out antics.

196
00:11:28.460 --> 00:11:30.722
So...

197
00:11:32.163 --> 00:11:34.498
Look. we're not
going anywhere. all right?

198
00:11:34.500 --> 00:11:36.595
And if you care
about your buddy.

199
00:11:36.597 --> 00:11:38.267
you'll let us
handle this.

200
00:11:38.269 --> 00:11:39.867
Mm.

201
00:11:42.173 --> 00:11:44.106
Nah. I think
I'm gonna be coming with you.

202
00:11:44.108 --> 00:11:45.642
Oh. the hell you are.

203
00:11:45.644 --> 00:11:47.705
I got contacts.
I can help.

204
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:49.344
You really can't.

205
00:11:49.346 --> 00:11:51.176
For example. a friend of mine
works military intelligence --

206
00:11:51.178 --> 00:11:53.176
owes me a favor.

207
00:11:55.753 --> 00:11:58.287
Would he know what Rick
and Kit's mission was?

208
00:11:58.289 --> 00:12:01.454
Sure. And he'd tell me
all about it.

209
00:12:03.224 --> 00:12:04.685
Okay. fine.

210
00:12:04.687 --> 00:12:07.223
No. it ain't.

211
00:12:07.225 --> 00:12:09.032
You know. I figure
what's going on here --

212
00:12:09.034 --> 00:12:11.666
I stick to you two
like flies on roadkill.

213
00:12:11.668 --> 00:12:13.971
make sure my buddy
comes home in one piece.

214
00:12:16.605 --> 00:12:17.971
Look. I know what you two
are thinking.

215
00:12:17.973 --> 00:12:20.209
but we are not gonna
hunt my best friend.

216
00:12:20.211 --> 00:12:22.837
who happens to be
a frigging war hero. by the way.

217
00:12:22.839 --> 00:12:25.276
We are gonna<i> find</i> him.

218
00:12:25.278 --> 00:12:27.244
And that's
the difference.

219
00:12:27.246 --> 00:12:28.875
Hey. man. we're right there
with you. okay?

220
00:12:28.877 --> 00:12:31.442
Kit's a hero. but --
but you got to prepare yourself.

221
00:12:31.444 --> 00:12:34.776
Kit might not be Kit anymore.

222
00:13:21.424 --> 00:13:22.661
Uh. sir?

223
00:13:24.831 --> 00:13:26.565
Sir. you have to pay
for that first!

224
00:13:29.432 --> 00:13:31.638
Hey.

225
00:13:38.909 --> 00:13:41.844
Now. look what you ma--

226
00:13:46.854 --> 00:13:48.284
Whoa!

227
00:13:49.854 --> 00:13:50.854
Hey!

228
00:14:07.844 --> 00:14:10.378
This guy just came in.
Get to the store. man.

229
00:14:11.348 --> 00:14:13.482
You got to hurry.

230
00:14:23.473 --> 00:14:25.638
Here you go.

231
00:14:27.480 --> 00:14:30.077
Yo. Sustenance.

232
00:14:30.079 --> 00:14:32.043
Listen. I got nothing
on cattle deaths.

233
00:14:32.045 --> 00:14:33.746
freakish weather --
none of it.

234
00:14:33.748 --> 00:14:37.618
So...
Probably not a demon.

235
00:14:37.620 --> 00:14:39.618
So maybe it's just not
your kind of thing at all.

236
00:14:39.620 --> 00:14:42.952
Well.
when in doubt...eat.

237
00:14:44.154 --> 00:14:45.521
Okay. here we go.

238
00:14:45.523 --> 00:14:48.426
I got an encrypted
e-mail here

239
00:14:48.428 --> 00:14:49.994
from my friend
at the M.I.

240
00:14:49.996 --> 00:14:51.393
And?

241
00:14:51.395 --> 00:14:53.130
Well...

242
00:14:53.132 --> 00:14:56.003
Kit and Rick were sent
to rescue an American P.O.W.

243
00:14:56.005 --> 00:14:59.042
Being held in Iraq --
the Najaf cemetery.

244
00:14:59.044 --> 00:15:01.338
Cemetery?

245
00:15:02.476 --> 00:15:05.113
Bastards use 'em as a. uh --
as a prison.

246
00:15:06.778 --> 00:15:09.511
I got some footage here from
the camera on Willis' helmet

247
00:15:09.513 --> 00:15:12.750
during his last mission
with Kit.

248
00:15:12.752 --> 00:15:13.950
<i>Okay. go!</i>

249
00:15:16.423 --> 00:15:18.790
<i>Down. Get down.</i>

250
00:15:20.454 --> 00:15:22.323
<i>Clear.</i>

251
00:15:22.325 --> 00:15:23.692
<i>Major Jones?!</i>

252
00:15:23.694 --> 00:15:25.492
<i>Major Matt Jones?</i>

253
00:15:27.094 --> 00:15:30.133
<i>Hey. right here.</i>
<i>Hey. Major Jones. is that you?</i>

254
00:15:30.135 --> 00:15:32.601
<i>Hey. Hey.</i>
<i>I'm captain Kit Verson.</i>

255
00:15:32.603 --> 00:15:34.010
<i>We're here</i>
<i>to bring you home. man.</i>

256
00:15:39.889 --> 00:15:42.056
<i>Oh. what the hell?!</i>

257
00:15:42.058 --> 00:15:43.993
<i>What the hell</i>
<i>was that?!</i>

258
00:15:47.963 --> 00:15:49.928
I'm guessing that didn't
have a happy ending.

259
00:15:49.930 --> 00:15:52.367
No. it did not.
Mission failed.

260
00:15:53.633 --> 00:15:55.703
And that P.O.W.
got shot by guards.

261
00:15:55.705 --> 00:15:59.438
Really?
That's what happened?

262
00:15:59.440 --> 00:16:02.036
That's the official story.

263
00:16:02.038 --> 00:16:04.970
All right. so. Kit and Rick
came back screwed-up.

264
00:16:04.972 --> 00:16:06.368
We know that much.

265
00:16:06.370 --> 00:16:09.205
Well. and then Rick jumped
the high dive.

266
00:16:09.207 --> 00:16:10.402
God. Kit.

267
00:16:11.939 --> 00:16:13.169
What was that?

268
00:16:13.171 --> 00:16:17.176
I set my phone
to get local alerts.

269
00:16:17.178 --> 00:16:18.774
Is it bad?

270
00:16:18.776 --> 00:16:20.710
It's bloody.

271
00:16:22.615 --> 00:16:25.309
All right.
let's get out of here.

272
00:16:34.485 --> 00:16:36.356
He licked the blood
off the floor?

273
00:16:36.358 --> 00:16:39.060
Yeah. the soda jockey back there
seemed pretty shook up by it.

274
00:16:39.062 --> 00:16:42.659
Now. the description he gave --
medium build. brown hair --

275
00:16:42.661 --> 00:16:44.667
that sound
like the Kit you know?

276
00:16:44.669 --> 00:16:47.297
Yeah. it does.
Great.

277
00:16:47.299 --> 00:16:50.736
So still sound like
it ain't our kind of thing?

278
00:16:54.938 --> 00:16:56.405
Hey. Jem.

279
00:16:56.407 --> 00:16:58.403
Cole. uh. the news said
someone was killed

280
00:16:58.405 --> 00:17:00.273
at the Gas 'n Sip
on Kenton.

281
00:17:00.275 --> 00:17:02.100
Yeah. I know.
I'm here right now.

282
00:17:02.102 --> 00:17:03.201
You are?

283
00:17:03.203 --> 00:17:05.462
W-what
are they saying?

284
00:17:05.464 --> 00:17:07.062
Not much. Look. Jem.

285
00:17:07.064 --> 00:17:09.237
Um. I really can't talk
right now. I'm sorry.

286
00:17:09.239 --> 00:17:10.565
Wait.

287
00:17:10.567 --> 00:17:14.235
Do they think that he --
that -- that Kit...

288
00:17:14.237 --> 00:17:15.634
Did this?

289
00:17:16.875 --> 00:17:18.241
I don't know.

290
00:17:19.537 --> 00:17:23.908
If he did.
he isn't in his right mind.

291
00:17:23.910 --> 00:17:25.940
and you know that.
Cole.

292
00:17:25.942 --> 00:17:27.708
You got to save him.

293
00:17:27.710 --> 00:17:30.546
I will.

294
00:17:30.548 --> 00:17:34.574
I know. And. uh...

295
00:17:34.576 --> 00:17:37.075
And that's the only thing
keeping me sane right now.

296
00:17:39.314 --> 00:17:40.709
I was thinking.
you know. sometimes.

297
00:17:40.711 --> 00:17:42.443
when Kit
wanted to be alone.

298
00:17:42.445 --> 00:17:45.347
he would head up north
to his dad's old cabin.

299
00:17:45.349 --> 00:17:47.146
Maybe you could
go check it out.

300
00:17:47.148 --> 00:17:49.745
and -- and -- and I'll stay here
in case he comes home.

301
00:17:49.747 --> 00:17:51.416
Right.

302
00:17:51.418 --> 00:17:53.751
Hey. Kung-Fu grip.
you coming?

303
00:17:53.753 --> 00:17:56.447
Hey. Jem. I got to go.

304
00:17:56.449 --> 00:17:58.224
So. what next?

305
00:17:58.226 --> 00:18:00.255
We hit every cop shop
within a 10-mile radius.

306
00:18:00.257 --> 00:18:02.221
put the word out. see
if we can't track him down.

307
00:18:02.223 --> 00:18:05.291
And if you find him.
what then?

308
00:18:08.594 --> 00:18:10.288
Kit needs help.

309
00:18:10.290 --> 00:18:13.758
He doesn't need a bullet.
and he doesn't need a knife.

310
00:18:15.927 --> 00:18:18.762
Okay.
You know what. Cole?

311
00:18:18.764 --> 00:18:20.760
We know you want to
protect your buddy. but --

312
00:18:20.762 --> 00:18:25.827
if he's a monster...
we got to put him down.

313
00:18:28.330 --> 00:18:30.327
That's the way
it's gonna have to be. huh?

314
00:18:30.329 --> 00:18:33.396
That's the job.

315
00:18:36.466 --> 00:18:39.262
So. you in or out?

316
00:18:53.031 --> 00:18:54.436
Thanks for the lift.

317
00:18:54.438 --> 00:18:56.131
It's better this way.
all right?

318
00:18:56.133 --> 00:18:58.171
You keep her calm.
We'll keep you posted.

319
00:18:58.173 --> 00:19:00.172
Yeah.

320
00:19:00.174 --> 00:19:01.972
Hey. Cole.

321
00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:04.444
He shows up.
don't try and be a hero.

322
00:19:04.446 --> 00:19:05.508
Call us.

323
00:19:05.510 --> 00:19:07.412
You got it.

324
00:19:40.098 --> 00:19:41.991
And you
bought him dinner.

325
00:20:08.154 --> 00:20:10.321
Kit?

326
00:20:23.669 --> 00:20:26.236
Hey. Kit?
Are you here?

327
00:20:26.238 --> 00:20:27.740
It's Cole.

328
00:20:27.742 --> 00:20:32.413
There's some real serious people
looking for you. Kit.

329
00:20:32.415 --> 00:20:34.244
And they won't
just want to talk.

330
00:20:46.659 --> 00:20:51.159
It's bad. Kit.

331
00:20:59.938 --> 00:21:02.904
And it's either me...

332
00:21:02.906 --> 00:21:05.502
or them.

333
00:21:15.678 --> 00:21:18.549
Hey. Kit.

334
00:21:18.551 --> 00:21:19.781
Hey.

335
00:21:19.783 --> 00:21:21.749
Hey. Kit.

336
00:21:22.951 --> 00:21:25.957
I'm sorry. I can't stop.
Aah!

337
00:21:48.508 --> 00:21:50.410
Wait. wait. wait!

338
00:22:02.588 --> 00:22:04.625
Oh. god.

339
00:22:17.698 --> 00:22:20.767
Oh. God.

340
00:22:20.769 --> 00:22:21.872
Ew.

341
00:22:21.874 --> 00:22:24.104
Something went down
my...throat.

342
00:22:24.106 --> 00:22:26.006
All right. Cole.
just try and stay calm.

343
00:22:26.008 --> 00:22:27.302
Oh. God.
Cole?

344
00:22:27.304 --> 00:22:28.909
Something moved.
It's alive. Sammy.

345
00:22:28.911 --> 00:22:30.742
All right. well. we're gonna
get it out of you. okay?

346
00:22:30.744 --> 00:22:32.847
How?!
We'll figure it out.

347
00:22:32.849 --> 00:22:35.511
We...

348
00:22:35.513 --> 00:22:37.784
Man. that was a dumbass move
coming here alone.

349
00:22:37.786 --> 00:22:39.352
You know that. right?

350
00:22:39.354 --> 00:22:41.287
Oh. I'm sorry. I should have
let the machete brothers

351
00:22:41.289 --> 00:22:42.549
cut my buddy's head off.

352
00:22:42.551 --> 00:22:43.917
Well. if you did.
maybe you wouldn't be

353
00:22:43.919 --> 00:22:45.620
choking down
a damn Khan worm right now.

354
00:22:45.622 --> 00:22:47.060
What's a Khan worm?

355
00:22:47.062 --> 00:22:48.228
You think
that's what it is?

356
00:22:48.230 --> 00:22:49.796
Or some sort
of freak cousin.

357
00:22:49.798 --> 00:22:51.427
Freak cousin of what?

358
00:22:51.429 --> 00:22:53.427
A couple years back.
Dean and I worked a case.

359
00:22:53.429 --> 00:22:55.426
We got stuck in a cannery
with this worm.

360
00:22:55.428 --> 00:22:58.162
It would get into people's bodies and --
It was freaking awful.

361
00:22:58.164 --> 00:22:59.801
All right. so you've been to this rodeo
before. How do we kill it?

362
00:23:02.874 --> 00:23:06.405
Worst case --
headshot the person it's in.

363
00:23:06.407 --> 00:23:09.468
Worm crawls out.
we stomp it like a bug.

364
00:23:09.470 --> 00:23:11.835
Is there a version
where you don't cap me?

365
00:23:14.444 --> 00:23:16.345
Yeah. uh. last time.

366
00:23:16.347 --> 00:23:18.344
electrocution made the worm
leave the body.

367
00:23:18.346 --> 00:23:22.144
All right. fine.
Electrocution it is. I'm game.

368
00:23:25.953 --> 00:23:28.656
All right.
You two get to work.

369
00:23:28.658 --> 00:23:29.752
I'll go look for Kit.

370
00:23:29.754 --> 00:23:31.192
Hey. hey. Sammy?
Yeah.

371
00:23:31.194 --> 00:23:34.529
If we can fix me.
we can save Kit. right?

372
00:23:34.531 --> 00:23:37.666
That's the idea.

373
00:23:41.235 --> 00:23:43.505
Mm.

374
00:23:43.507 --> 00:23:45.504
You know that this is gonna hurt
like a son of a bitch?

375
00:23:47.338 --> 00:23:50.471
Hell. I have a wife.
a kid.

376
00:23:50.473 --> 00:23:53.109
and an upside-down mortgage
to get back to.

377
00:23:53.111 --> 00:23:56.409
Whatever it takes.
Dean-o.

378
00:23:56.411 --> 00:23:58.009
Okay.

379
00:23:58.011 --> 00:24:00.343
Mm.

380
00:24:00.345 --> 00:24:04.141
So. last time
you saw this thing.

381
00:24:04.143 --> 00:24:06.612
it turned people
into killers. too?

382
00:24:06.614 --> 00:24:09.980
Yeah. except that one did
a mind-control number on us.

383
00:24:09.982 --> 00:24:13.284
Damn.

384
00:24:13.286 --> 00:24:17.492
Day in. day out. you and Sammy
saving people from things

385
00:24:17.494 --> 00:24:19.829
they just can't
wrap their minds around...

386
00:24:19.831 --> 00:24:22.693
Hell. and nobody
even notices it.

387
00:24:24.430 --> 00:24:28.234
Hell. at least I get a medal
for my efforts.

388
00:24:28.236 --> 00:24:30.829
But you...

389
00:24:30.831 --> 00:24:33.029
I tried
to kill your ass.

390
00:24:33.031 --> 00:24:36.604
Yeah.
Well. good times.

391
00:24:36.606 --> 00:24:39.436
I almost
took you off the map.

392
00:24:39.438 --> 00:24:42.003
Who would be
saving me now?

393
00:24:42.005 --> 00:24:46.274
Yeah. well. let's not get
too sentimental about it.

394
00:24:46.276 --> 00:24:49.510
All right.
let's fire this puppy up.

395
00:24:49.512 --> 00:24:51.613
Well. you say that
like it's just another Tuesday.

396
00:24:51.615 --> 00:24:55.644
Oh. buddy.
it's only Monday.

397
00:25:01.857 --> 00:25:04.822
All right.

398
00:25:24.442 --> 00:25:26.303
Anything?

399
00:25:26.305 --> 00:25:28.174
Last time.
it came out of our ears.

400
00:25:28.176 --> 00:25:30.771
And...?

401
00:25:30.773 --> 00:25:32.538
I'm not
seeing anything yet.

402
00:25:32.540 --> 00:25:35.041
Do it again.

403
00:25:47.487 --> 00:25:50.421
All right. that sucker
should have crawled out by now.

404
00:25:50.423 --> 00:25:52.387
Again.

405
00:25:52.389 --> 00:25:54.458
I keep going.
this is gonna kill you.

406
00:25:54.460 --> 00:25:55.458
Again!

407
00:26:18.076 --> 00:26:19.370
Cole.

408
00:26:19.372 --> 00:26:22.840
Hey. hey.

409
00:26:22.842 --> 00:26:26.409
Cole!
Come on. Come on.

410
00:26:27.578 --> 00:26:29.216
Cole!

411
00:26:34.185 --> 00:26:37.183
Hey.
Hey! Hey! Okay!

412
00:26:39.321 --> 00:26:42.791
Hey.

413
00:26:42.793 --> 00:26:45.199
All right. Again.

414
00:26:45.201 --> 00:26:47.597
No. No. we're done
playing "Operation."

415
00:26:47.599 --> 00:26:49.598
I zap you again.
you're toast.

416
00:26:51.968 --> 00:26:53.902
Just take a knee.

417
00:27:08.888 --> 00:27:10.487
Dean.

418
00:27:10.489 --> 00:27:12.793
How did it go?
Worm was a no-show.

419
00:27:12.795 --> 00:27:14.625
That doesn't make any sense.
Last time --

420
00:27:14.627 --> 00:27:16.096
Well. this ain't
the last time.

421
00:27:16.098 --> 00:27:17.663
I mean. maybe this is
a whole new species. you know?

422
00:27:17.665 --> 00:27:19.662
All I know
is that sparky struck out.

423
00:27:19.664 --> 00:27:21.398
Well. there's got to
be something.

424
00:27:21.400 --> 00:27:23.102
I mean. everything
has a weakness. right?

425
00:27:23.104 --> 00:27:25.670
Well. what about you?
Any luck?

426
00:27:25.672 --> 00:27:27.270
I'm on my way
to Kit's.

427
00:27:27.272 --> 00:27:28.670
Thought I'd check
there first.

428
00:27:28.672 --> 00:27:31.805
All right. well...
Hurry up. man.

429
00:27:31.807 --> 00:27:34.340
You got it.

430
00:27:36.550 --> 00:27:38.116
You okay?

431
00:27:38.118 --> 00:27:40.612
So this is what
in over your head looks like.

432
00:27:42.582 --> 00:27:44.116
Just got to keep your head
in the game.

433
00:27:45.686 --> 00:27:49.092
Okay. what do we know
about this thing?

434
00:27:49.094 --> 00:27:51.660
Uh.
sucker dries you out.

435
00:27:52.998 --> 00:27:55.196
I'm thirsty already.
man.

436
00:27:55.198 --> 00:27:57.628
It likes water.

437
00:27:57.630 --> 00:27:59.636
Then when
that's not enough...

438
00:27:59.638 --> 00:28:01.172
Blood. I don't know.

439
00:28:01.174 --> 00:28:05.274
Maybe lack of fluids
makes the thing hostile.

440
00:28:05.276 --> 00:28:06.536
So it's like
a parasite.

441
00:28:06.538 --> 00:28:08.039
It wrings you dry.
and then it moves on.

442
00:28:08.041 --> 00:28:10.669
So if I dry myself out.

443
00:28:10.671 --> 00:28:12.237
the son of a bitch wouldn't like
that very much. now. would he?

444
00:28:12.239 --> 00:28:14.203
No. he'd want
the hell out.

445
00:28:14.205 --> 00:28:15.570
You'd be
a hostile environment --

446
00:28:15.572 --> 00:28:17.608
well. more than
you already are.

447
00:28:17.610 --> 00:28:22.976
Well. to be fair. you really
haven't seen my chiller side.

448
00:28:24.314 --> 00:28:26.553
What do you think
about rapid dehydration?

449
00:28:26.555 --> 00:28:30.419
Big fan.

450
00:28:32.157 --> 00:28:35.259
Just make sure you squash
that sucker when it goes AWOL.

451
00:28:35.261 --> 00:28:37.731
Sounds like a plan.

452
00:28:39.933 --> 00:28:43.342
All right.

453
00:28:43.344 --> 00:28:45.910
Nothing like a sweat lodge
in the woods. huh?

454
00:29:13.353 --> 00:29:14.520
Kit?

455
00:29:21.065 --> 00:29:22.431
Honey.

456
00:29:22.433 --> 00:29:25.431
Look at me.

457
00:29:29.340 --> 00:29:31.948
What's happened
to you?

458
00:29:34.917 --> 00:29:36.849
Listen.

459
00:29:36.851 --> 00:29:42.488
Whatever happened.
whatever you...

460
00:29:42.490 --> 00:29:45.155
You did...

461
00:29:45.157 --> 00:29:48.963
We're gonna fix this.
okay?

462
00:29:48.965 --> 00:29:52.266
We're gonna
get you well.

463
00:29:52.268 --> 00:29:55.769
Baby.

464
00:29:55.771 --> 00:29:59.233
Kit! Aah!

465
00:29:59.235 --> 00:30:01.203
Kit. stop!
Please!

466
00:30:01.205 --> 00:30:05.676
I can't...stop.

467
00:30:10.949 --> 00:30:13.321
Are you okay?

468
00:30:13.323 --> 00:30:14.651
Yeah.

469
00:30:27.938 --> 00:30:29.840
You're in a...
Sweat lodge?

470
00:30:29.842 --> 00:30:31.105
Well. you're the one

471
00:30:31.107 --> 00:30:32.545
who said everything
has got a weakness.

472
00:30:32.547 --> 00:30:34.978
So I figure take a schvitz.
kill a freak.

473
00:30:34.980 --> 00:30:36.650
Call that a good day.

474
00:30:36.652 --> 00:30:37.945
Yeah. if it works.

475
00:30:37.947 --> 00:30:40.384
Well.
you got a better idea?

476
00:30:40.386 --> 00:30:42.584
Yeah. I do.
actually. Dean.

477
00:30:42.586 --> 00:30:45.457
We know
how to end this.

478
00:30:46.924 --> 00:30:48.530
Yeah.
plan "B" for "bullet."

479
00:30:48.532 --> 00:30:51.163
But we're not quite there yet.
so just hold tight.

480
00:30:51.165 --> 00:30:52.363
All right.

481
00:30:52.365 --> 00:30:54.330
How's the wife?

482
00:30:55.540 --> 00:31:00.104
She's barely holding on.
How's Cole?

483
00:31:01.138 --> 00:31:02.776
He's going strong.

484
00:31:02.778 --> 00:31:04.378
Good.

485
00:31:04.380 --> 00:31:07.317
Look. Dean.
Kit is gonna come to.

486
00:31:07.319 --> 00:31:09.349
And when I got here.
it was bad.

487
00:31:09.351 --> 00:31:11.618
We're on the clock.
I get it.

488
00:31:11.620 --> 00:31:14.553
Yeah.

489
00:31:19.693 --> 00:31:21.964
Just keep sweating. man.
You're doing great.

490
00:31:31.238 --> 00:31:32.805
Sorry.

491
00:31:34.583 --> 00:31:36.109
I don't understand.

492
00:31:36.111 --> 00:31:40.483
On Kit's last mission.
on his deployment with Rick.

493
00:31:40.485 --> 00:31:45.648
there was an incident.
and something got inside Kit.

494
00:31:45.650 --> 00:31:50.390
I mean.
h-have you seen anything?

495
00:31:50.392 --> 00:31:53.925
I mean. y--
I saw<i> something.</i> okay?

496
00:31:53.927 --> 00:31:55.988
But it -- it was...

497
00:31:55.990 --> 00:31:57.828
It was a monster.

498
00:31:57.830 --> 00:32:02.731
It was a real-life.
actual. honest-to-god monster.

499
00:32:02.733 --> 00:32:05.793
And your husband...

500
00:32:08.328 --> 00:32:11.596
...it changed him.

501
00:32:11.598 --> 00:32:15.401
What?

502
00:32:15.403 --> 00:32:17.231
Who are you?

503
00:32:42.520 --> 00:32:47.419
My dad...He got something
inside him. too. right?

504
00:32:49.653 --> 00:32:54.826
You think this is what
he felt like when he turned?

505
00:32:54.828 --> 00:32:58.196
Maybe.

506
00:32:58.198 --> 00:33:02.132
I mean. he was human
before he was...a monster.

507
00:33:04.574 --> 00:33:07.205
I get it...

508
00:33:07.207 --> 00:33:09.405
Why you did it. Dean.

509
00:33:09.407 --> 00:33:12.077
My dad wasn't
my dad anymore.

510
00:33:13.312 --> 00:33:15.518
If I go down
that same road...

511
00:33:15.520 --> 00:33:19.487
I want you
to do that to me. too.

512
00:33:20.994 --> 00:33:23.255
That road?

513
00:33:23.257 --> 00:33:25.263
That means giving up.

514
00:33:25.265 --> 00:33:27.863
If you think
that's where you're headed.

515
00:33:27.865 --> 00:33:29.664
then you've got it
ass-backwards.

516
00:33:29.666 --> 00:33:34.903
You're gonna fight harder
than you ever have.

517
00:33:34.905 --> 00:33:36.567
You understand?

518
00:33:44.785 --> 00:33:47.446
Ahh.

519
00:33:47.448 --> 00:33:51.687
Dean-o.

520
00:33:55.160 --> 00:33:59.895
Will you do me the honor
of tying me to this chair?

521
00:34:04.367 --> 00:34:06.333
Yeah.

522
00:34:29.016 --> 00:34:30.982
Aah!

523
00:34:30.984 --> 00:34:33.391
Come on. We both know
you're not gonna do it.

524
00:34:33.393 --> 00:34:37.054
You are gonna sweat
this one through.

525
00:34:37.056 --> 00:34:38.662
I can't. Dean!

526
00:34:38.664 --> 00:34:40.695
Yes. you can.

527
00:34:40.697 --> 00:34:42.632
Listen to me.
Yes. you can.

528
00:34:42.634 --> 00:34:44.665
Think about
your family. hmm?

529
00:34:44.667 --> 00:34:49.139
Your wife. your kid.
You hear me?

530
00:34:49.141 --> 00:34:52.147
I appreciate the talk.
coach.

531
00:34:52.149 --> 00:34:53.715
But honestly.
all I can think about

532
00:34:53.717 --> 00:34:56.947
is slicing your wrist and
drinking you like a fountain.

533
00:34:59.389 --> 00:35:01.356
I guess that makes me
a monster. don't it?

534
00:35:09.690 --> 00:35:11.096
So.
you're a hunter.

535
00:35:11.098 --> 00:35:13.159
Right.
And...

536
00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:17.229
I'm sorry. This is gonna
take me a minute.

537
00:35:17.231 --> 00:35:19.869
It's. uh...

538
00:35:19.871 --> 00:35:23.269
It's crazy. right?
It sounds crazy? I know.

539
00:35:23.271 --> 00:35:25.005
But it's the truth.

540
00:35:28.079 --> 00:35:32.445
I don't care if he's
what you say he is. okay?

541
00:35:32.447 --> 00:35:33.781
He's my husband.

542
00:35:33.783 --> 00:35:35.381
Jemma.
he tried to kill you.

543
00:35:35.383 --> 00:35:38.821
Was that your husband
when you looked into his eyes?

544
00:35:38.823 --> 00:35:40.022
Was that
the Kit you know?

545
00:35:40.024 --> 00:35:43.857
Look...Dean is working
on it.

546
00:35:43.859 --> 00:35:46.234
Dean and Cole
will figure it out. okay?

547
00:35:46.236 --> 00:35:47.762
Let me check in
with them.

548
00:35:47.764 --> 00:35:49.898
All right.

549
00:35:51.236 --> 00:35:54.603
Sam. Sam.

550
00:36:06.622 --> 00:36:07.957
Sam.

551
00:37:09.581 --> 00:37:11.586
Come on. Sammy!
Pick up!

552
00:37:16.557 --> 00:37:19.059
Don't make me
pull this trigger.

553
00:37:19.061 --> 00:37:20.731
I already did.

554
00:37:27.898 --> 00:37:29.534
Holy...

555
00:37:50.351 --> 00:37:52.189
You okay?

556
00:37:52.191 --> 00:37:56.022
Yeah.
Oh. thank God.

557
00:37:56.024 --> 00:37:58.429
Thank God.

558
00:38:03.432 --> 00:38:04.734
Hey.

559
00:38:04.736 --> 00:38:08.134
Sammy. we did it.
Cole's all right.

560
00:38:08.136 --> 00:38:12.005
Get Kit over here
as soon as you can.

561
00:38:12.007 --> 00:38:15.339
It's too late.

562
00:38:44.516 --> 00:38:46.346
Hey. Cole.

563
00:38:49.157 --> 00:38:51.756
Listen. uh. I. uh...

564
00:38:52.094 --> 00:38:55.292
For whatever
it's worth...

565
00:38:55.294 --> 00:38:57.302
I really wish
it hadn't ended this way.

566
00:38:57.304 --> 00:39:00.704
Yeah. me. too. Sammy boy.

567
00:39:02.209 --> 00:39:05.407
I mean. Kit --
he was gonna kill her and --

568
00:39:05.409 --> 00:39:08.076
I know.
Jemma told me everything.

569
00:39:10.541 --> 00:39:13.410
Solider goes crazy.
attacks his wife.

570
00:39:13.412 --> 00:39:15.945
She had to kill him.

571
00:39:15.947 --> 00:39:19.680
Or at least that's the story
that she's got to tell.

572
00:39:23.492 --> 00:39:26.490
I guess
I've seen it all now.

573
00:39:26.492 --> 00:39:30.192
Some. Not all.

574
00:39:32.193 --> 00:39:35.231
I just want to go home.
see my family.

575
00:39:40.368 --> 00:39:43.330
I want to thank you. Dean-o.
for keeping me standing.

576
00:39:43.332 --> 00:39:46.031
Well. all it took
was a little

577
00:39:46.033 --> 00:39:48.230
blood. sweat.
and. uh. more sweat.

578
00:39:50.169 --> 00:39:53.038
You take care of yourself.
you hear?

579
00:39:53.040 --> 00:39:56.939
All right. I will.

580
00:39:56.941 --> 00:39:59.739
But I still hope I don't
see the two of you anymore.

581
00:40:01.382 --> 00:40:02.845
No offense.

582
00:40:04.215 --> 00:40:05.852
None taken.

583
00:40:25.368 --> 00:40:28.270
don't blame yourself
for Kit. man.

584
00:40:30.567 --> 00:40:34.204
I can't help it. Dean.
It feels crappy.

585
00:40:34.206 --> 00:40:36.909
I know it does.

586
00:40:39.743 --> 00:40:42.317
I tried. I did.

587
00:40:42.319 --> 00:40:45.347
I tried. I just...

588
00:40:45.349 --> 00:40:47.988
I couldn't save
this one.

589
00:40:51.991 --> 00:40:53.956
You know.
you can do everything right.

590
00:40:53.958 --> 00:40:58.026
And even still.
sometimes...

591
00:40:58.028 --> 00:41:00.297
The guy still dies.

592
00:41:20.012 --> 00:41:26.512
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
